---
title: "getAssetOutAmount (Payment Abstraction V2)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_validate: validate preconditions
    q_validate --> q_step1: amountIn > 0 AND assetInUsdPrice > 0
    q_validate --> q_error: precondition violated
    q_error --> [*]: revert

    q_step1 --> q_step2: usdValue = mulDivUp(amountIn, assetInUsdPrice, 10^assetInDecimals)
    q_step2 --> q_calc_multiplier: adjustedValue = mulWadUp(usdValue, priceMultiplier)

    q_calc_multiplier --> q_elapsed: elapsed = block.timestamp - auctionStart
    q_elapsed --> q_decay: decayRate = (startMultiplier - endMultiplier) / auctionDuration
    q_decay --> q_price: priceMultiplier = startMultiplier - decayRate * elapsed
    q_price --> q_clamp_high: priceMultiplier > startMultiplier
    q_clamp_high --> q_step3: priceMultiplier = startMultiplier
    q_price --> q_clamp_low: priceMultiplier < endMultiplier
    q_clamp_low --> q_step3: priceMultiplier = endMultiplier
    q_price --> q_step3: endMultiplier <= priceMultiplier <= startMultiplier

    q_step3 --> [*]: assetOutAmount = mulDivUp(adjustedValue, 10^assetOutDecimals, assetOutUsdPrice)

    note right of q_step1
        INV-001: assetOutAmount >= 1 for all valid inputs (proven by rounding-up chain)
        INV-002: priceMultiplier is bounded between endingPriceMultiplier and startingPriceMultiplier
        INV-003: all rounding operations are in protocol favor (round up)
        INV-004: decayRate is rounded down to avoid exceeding maximum discount
    end note
